  "body": "## üéâ Description\r\nWhitelists and other access/validation functionalities should be standalone contracts, independent of crowdsale contracts. The rationale is that other types of contracts (e.g. gouvernement, exchanges, +18y/o games) might want to implement some sort of access control logic gates. I would suggest rewriting some of contracts along these lines. For instance, [WhitelistedCrowdsale.sol](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/crowdsale/validation/WhitelistedCrowdsale.sol) could be rewritten as `Whitelisted.sol`, like [this](https://gist.github.com/PhABC/cf0e8167e493d8758b46eecbf15dfd87). A Whistelisted contract could then be set to `WhitelistedCrowdsale is Whitelisted, Crowdsale, Ownable { ... }`. \r\n\r\n- [ ] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [x] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n",
